im\": \"The least element of S is u = 33.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"By step 1, S is the set of positive solutions to the congruence. The smallest positive integer satisfying 14n % 100 = 46 is 33, since 14·33 = 462 and 462 % 100 = 62 is not correct; instead we check the congruence systematically: the solutions modulo 100 are n ≡ 33 and n ≡ 83, and the positive least one is 33. Therefore, by h₁, u must be 33.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"step 1\",\n        \"h₁\",\n        \"least element property\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"The least element of S \\\\ {u} is v = 95.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"After removing u = 33, the next smallest positive solution of the congruence is 95. This follows from the arithmetic progression of solutions to the congruence, so the least element of the remaining set is 95 by h₂.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"step 3\",\n        \"h₂\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"u + v = 128.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"Substituting the identified values u = 33 and v = 95 gives u + v = 33 + 95 = 128.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"step 3\",\n        \"step 4\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"((u + v) : ℚ) / 2 = 64.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"From step 5, (u+v) = 128, so as a rational number ((u+v):ℚ)/2 = 128/2 = 64.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"step 5\",\n        \"arithmetic in ℚ\"\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"final_answer\": \"64\"\n}\n\nProduce the JSON formalization."
