ral number n.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"From step 2, the residues modulo 7 repeat after 16 terms: the block from 0 to 15 is followed by the same starting residues again. This establishes period 16 modulo 7 for the sequence t.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"step 2\",\n        \"periodicity of Fibonacci modulo 7\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"t a ≡ t 5 [MOD 7], t b ≡ t 10 [MOD 7], and t c ≡ t 15 [MOD 7].\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"The congruences h₃, h₄, and h₅ say that a ≡ 5, b ≡ 10, and c ≡ 15 modulo 16. By step 3, changing the index by a multiple of 16 does not change the value modulo 7, so the corresponding t-values are congruent modulo 7.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"h₃\",\n        \"h₄\",\n        \"h₅\",\n        \"step 3\",\n        \"congruence compatibility\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"claim\": \"(t a + t b + t c) % 7 = 5.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"By step 4, the sum is congruent modulo 7 to t 5 + t 10 + t 15. From step 2, these are 5, 6, and 1 modulo 7, so their sum is 12 ≡ 5 mod 7. Hence the remainder upon division by 7 is 5.\",\n      \"facts_used\": [\n        \"step 2\",\n        \"step 4\",\n        \"modular addition\"\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"final_answer\": \"5\"\n}\n\nProduce the JSON formalization."
